From 1920640198362c45c1bf6860425939f8b20d787b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Roopni Devanathan <rdevanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Jul 2025 11:53:49 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:wifi: ath12k: Hold wiphy lock before calling
 wdev_chandef()

Callers of wdev_chandef() are expected to hold wiphy lock before calling
the API, because it returns channel definition based on the mode of the
wireless device. But the worker cfg80211_propagate_cac_done_wk() does not
hold the lock before calling wdev_chandef(). This causes warning in hwsim
test case that validates domain change in DFS channel.

Workqueue: cfg80211 cfg80211_propagate_cac_done_wk [cfg80211]
Call Trace:
 um_set_signals+0x0/0x3c
 um_set_signals+0x0/0x3c
 _printk+0x0/0x9f
 dump_stack_lvl+0x47/0x52
 __warn+0xe1/0x112
 lock_acquire+0xd0/0x146
 mac80211_hwsim_config+0x176/0x2ed [mac80211_hwsim]
 warn_slowpath_fmt+0xd6/0xe2
 mac80211_hwsim_config+0x26e/0x2ed [mac80211_hwsim]
 lock_release+0xc0/0x25f
 warn_slowpath_fmt+0x0/0xe2
 unblock_signals+0x36/0xe0
 um_set_signals+0x28/0x3c
 um_set_signals+0x0/0x3c
 lock_is_held_type+0x147/0x15f
 hrtimer_try_to_cancel+0x1d/0x9c
 __ieee80211_recalc_idle+0x59/0x10d [mac80211]
 ieee80211_recalc_idle+0x1b/0x3b [mac80211]
 ieee80211_del_chanctx+0x106/0x120 [mac80211]
 ieee80211_free_chanctx+0xd7/0x12e [mac80211]
 __ieee80211_link_release_channel+0x100/0x12c [mac80211]
 hrtimer_cancel+0x0/0x49
 ieee80211_end_cac+0xda/0xf5 [mac80211]
 regulatory_propagate_dfs_state+0x27a/0x294 [cfg80211]
 lock_release+0x0/0x25f
 _raw_spin_lock_irq+0x0/0x4a
 process_one_work+0x211/0x477
 cfg80211_propagate_cac_done_wk+0x35/0x42 [cfg80211]

Fix this by holding lock before calling wdev_chandef() in the API -
cfg80211_check_and_end_cac().

Patch-dependency: None
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Roopni Devanathan <rdevanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/wireless/reg.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/wireless/reg.c b/net/wireless/reg.c
index ce5e16c..5a93e93 100644
--- a/net/wireless/reg.c
+++ b/net/wireless/reg.c
@@ -4370,6 +4370,8 @@ static void cfg80211_check_and_end_cac(struct cfg80211_registered_device *rdev)
 	struct wireless_dev *wdev;
 	unsigned int link_id;
 
+	guard(wiphy)(&rdev->wiphy);
+
 	/* If we finished CAC or received radar, we should end any
 	 * CAC running on the same channels.
 	 * the check !cfg80211_chandef_dfs_usable contain 2 options:
-- 
2.34.1

